The Michigan Chain of Lakes is a series of interconnected lakes and rivers located in the northern part of the Lower Peninsula of Michigan. The chain includes a total of 14 lakes, which are:

Lake Bellaire
Clam Lake
Torch Lake
Lake Skegemog
Elk Lake
Lake Michigan
Intermediate Lake
Six Mile Lake
St. Clair Lake
Benway Lake
Hanley Lake
Wilson Lake
Intermediate River
Grass River
These lakes offer a wide range of recreational opportunities, including boating, fishing, swimming, and kayaking, and are popular destinations for vacationers and residents alike.